Yahoo Finds Ad Agency in China 
The Internet content provider Yahoo has authorized the Beijing-based
Infoshare Technology Co. Ltd. to be its exclusive advertising agency in
China.
According to an agreement inked today between Yahoo and Infoshare, the
latter will promote Yahoo services in China and help Chinese customers
create on-line advertisements on Yahoo's worldwide network.
Infoshare is an Internet service company funded by the China
International Electronic Commerce Center. The company designed and
built the "Made-in-China" web market and China's Ministry of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation web site.
A Chinese textile exporter and a local town government have signed
agreements with Infoshare to display their ads and economic and
investment information on Yahoo's global network, according to reports.
